the company follows accounting principles board opinion 25, accounting for
stock issued to employees, to account for stock option and employee stock purchase plans. an alternative method of accounting for stock options is sfas 123, accounting for stock-based compensation. employee stock options are valued at
grant date using the black-scholes valuation model, and this compensation cost is recognized ratably over the vesting period.
