note 16earnings per share   basic earnings per share is computed on the basis of the weighted average number of common shares outstanding. diluted earnings per share is computed on the basis of the
weighted average number of common shares outstanding plus the effect of outstanding preferred shares using the if-converted method, outstanding put warrants using the reverse treasury stock method, and outstanding stock
options using the treasury stock method.  the components of basic and diluted earnings per share were as follows:
